 Syntax:  .ignore <message_type>   or   .ignore all

Results:  Stops specified message types from appearing in your screen. 
          Where <message_type> is the type of message ignored.  This command is 
          useful if you wish to read the message boards or the news without 
          trying to keep up with speech appearing on the screen.
         .ignore all will ignore all messages.
              
   Note:  To listen to all messages again, type --> .listen all

Example:  To ignore shout messages, type --> .ignore shouts

  Types:  all afks says logs shouts knocks messages topics kills
          bcasts moves echos greets picture fights atmos wiztells
          succs fails nerfs roomdescs beeps tictactoes tells colornames

See also: listen
